      "writtenOn": "2021-04-09T16:07:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "NativeAllocationRegistry isn\u0027t public so you can\u0027t use that.  Finalizers are a good option, but I think it is good practice to have a \"release\" or \"recycle\" method that users can call to free up the memory explicitly instead of waiting on the GC to do it.",
